00:28:40,416 --> 00:28:41,166
What's wrong?

591
00:28:41,916 --> 00:28:42,583
Is something the matter?

592
00:28:44,250 --> 00:28:45,041
Teacher

593
00:28:45,458 --> 00:28:46,500
I want to ask something.

594
00:28:46,500 --> 00:28:48,500
You said you'd check the surveillance about yesterday.

595
00:28:48,708 --> 00:28:50,333
Is there any result now?

596
00:28:55,958 --> 00:28:58,125
Did you find the person who stole the Walkman?

597
00:29:01,625 --> 00:29:02,791
Who was it?

598
00:29:07,708 --> 00:29:08,500
Chen Jing'an

599
00:29:09,125 --> 00:29:10,791
Let me explain.

600
00:29:11,208 --> 00:29:12,000
Well,

601
00:29:12,625 --> 00:29:13,916
about this matter,

602
00:29:14,125 --> 00:29:16,458
it's not a small issue, but it's not exactly huge either.

603
00:29:17,500 --> 00:29:19,208
For the sake of that student,

604
00:29:19,791 --> 00:29:22,125
I can't tell you who it is for now.

605
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:24,208
But you have to trust me.

606
00:29:24,666 --> 00:29:25,916
Give me a little more time.

607
00:29:26,125 --> 00:29:27,500
I will definitely give you

608
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:28,416
a proper explanation.

609
00:29:28,416 --> 00:29:29,125
Alright?

610
00:29:30,666 --> 00:29:31,708
Teacher Yu

611
00:29:32,083 --> 00:29:32,666
Actually,

612
00:29:33,041 --> 00:29:34,416
I just wanted to ask,

613
00:29:35,291 --> 00:29:36,125
that person,

614
00:29:36,791 --> 00:29:38,333
is it Deng Shasha?

615
00:29:40,125 --> 00:29:40,833
It's not her.

616
00:29:41,083 --> 00:29:42,000
It's not her.

617
00:29:42,708 --> 00:29:43,458
That's good.

618
00:29:43,583 --> 00:29:44,375
Thank you, teacher.

619
00:29:44,666 --> 00:29:46,916
Then I'll go now, thank you.

620
00:29:49,041 --> 00:29:50,916
It's really hot today.

621
00:30:16,583 --> 00:30:17,291
Liu Xinyi

622
00:30:21,250 --> 00:30:21,833
Thanks.

623
00:30:24,041 --> 00:30:25,000
Xinyi.

624
00:30:25,458 --> 00:30:27,083
Chen Changning knows your name.

625
00:30:27,583 --> 00:30:28,166
Maybe.

626
00:30:28,166 --> 00:30:29,708
He must've heard it at some point.

627
00:30:30,166 --> 00:30:31,375
Maybe he's interested in you.

628
00:30:31,375 --> 00:30:32,666
Maybe he's secretly paying attention to you.

629
00:30:32,833 --> 00:30:33,833
Don't talk nonsense.

630
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:36,458
Let's go.

631
00:30:40,416 --> 00:30:41,583
I was just looking for you.

632
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:43,416
Why were you looking for me?

633
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:45,750
I just asked Teacher Yu about checking the surveillance footage.

634
00:30:46,666 --> 00:30:47,875
What does that have to do with me?

635
00:30:48,791 --> 00:30:50,208
Teacher Yu said it wasn't Shasha.

636
00:30:52,541 --> 00:30:53,250
It wasn't her.

637
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:57,666
I have no reason to lie to you about this.

638
00:30:58,166 --> 00:30:59,958
Although Teacher Yu didn't tell me who it was,

639
00:30:59,958 --> 00:31:01,458
she's sure it wasn't Shasha.

640
00:31:01,458 --> 00:31:02,791
We really misunderstood her.

641
00:31:02,791 --> 00:31:03,625
Then...

642
00:31:05,041 --> 00:31:06,250
Why didn't she explain earlier?

643
00:31:08,583 --> 00:31:09,875
Because in her eyes,

644
00:31:10,083 --> 00:31:11,958
the person who misunderstood her is her best friend.

645
00:31:14,291 --> 00:31:15,083
I really don't get it.

646
00:31:15,083 --> 00:31:15,875
You girls...

647
00:31:15,875 --> 00:31:16,958
always say one thing and mean another.

648
00:31:17,083 --> 00:31:18,041
If she had explained earlier,

649
00:31:18,041 --> 00:31:19,416
none of this would've happened.

650
00:31:22,208 --> 00:31:23,166
Because she knew

651
00:31:23,541 --> 00:31:24,416
you wouldn't believe her.

652
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,250
So explaining wouldn't help.

653
00:31:28,791 --> 00:31:30,416
Why is everything so complicated?

654
00:31:39,083 --> 00:31:40,083
What's wrong?

655
00:31:40,583 --> 00:31:41,708
You've been scratching for a whole class.

656
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:42,791
My scalp is itchy.

657
00:31:45,166 --> 00:31:46,208
You're the one with an itchy scalp.

658
00:31:51,541 --> 00:31:53,208
About that thing with the Walkman before,

659
00:31:53,291 --> 00:31:54,875
I think I really misunderstood Deng Shasha.

660
00:31:55,666 --> 00:31:56,458
If it were you,

661
00:31:56,833 --> 00:31:57,500
what would you do?

662
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:01,458
I’d definitely point at your nose and yell at you.

663
00:32:01,541 --> 00:32:02,041
And then

664
00:32:02,625 --> 00:32:03,166
I’d cut ties with you.

665
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:04,500
Me?

666
00:32:05,458 --> 00:32:06,041
Watch your image.

667
00:32:13,458 --> 00:32:14,583
I was just kidding.

668
00:32:15,333 --> 00:32:17,875
But if it were me,

669
00:32:19,875 --> 00:32:21,125
I might even feel like dying.

670
00:32:22,333 --> 00:32:23,875
After all, we’ve known each other for so long.

671
00:32:25,166 --> 00:32:26,625
Even if everyone else misunderstood me,

672
00:32:27,333 --> 00:32:28,125
I’d still believe

673
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:30,333
that you would trust me unconditionally.

674
00:32:31,833 --> 00:32:33,958
But if you really did misunderstand me,

675
00:32:38,375 --> 00:32:39,750
I wouldn’t let you off even as a ghost.

676
00:32:42,666 --> 00:32:43,250
What if

677
00:32:43,750 --> 00:32:44,916
you’re not a ghost?

678
00:32:45,708 --> 00:32:46,625
What would you do?

679
00:32:49,625 --> 00:32:50,791
If you

680
00:32:51,250 --> 00:32:52,500
cried and begged,

681
00:32:53,041 --> 00:32:53,875
tried to please me,

682
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:55,583
apologized,

683
00:32:56,291 --> 00:32:56,875
and admitted you were wrong,

684
00:32:58,041 --> 00:32:59,666
I might consider forgiving you.

685
00:33:00,416 --> 00:33:01,541
Be serious, will you?

686
00:33:04,166 --> 00:33:05,666
Why are you hitting me?

687
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:08,791
Be a bit more serious.

688
00:33:09,125 --> 00:33:09,916
I think

689
00:33:10,583 --> 00:33:11,458
if you’ve never argued

690
00:33:11,875 --> 00:33:12,750
or had misunderstandings,

691
00:33:12,916 --> 00:33:13,833
you’re not real friends.

692
00:33:15,291 --> 00:33:16,041
The key is,

693
00:33:16,166 --> 00:33:17,250
after you’ve argued,

694
00:33:17,958 --> 00:33:18,541
you have to

695
00:33:18,666 --> 00:33:19,958
reflect on your own mistakes

696
00:33:20,708 --> 00:33:22,333
and honestly face the misunderstanding.

697
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,416
That’s how friendship lasts forever.

698
00:33:30,375 --> 00:33:31,041
Did you forget

699
00:33:31,666 --> 00:33:32,833
how the two of us made it through back then?

700
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:35,083
If we hadn't argued so much back then,

701
00:33:35,666 --> 00:33:36,958
would we have the relationship we do now?

702
00:33:38,125 --> 00:33:39,458
I don't even want to mention what happened to you.

703
00:33:39,458 --> 00:33:40,291
Let me tell you,

704
00:33:49,750 --> 00:33:51,375
I'm not really Zhu Niannian.

705
00:33:52,291 --> 00:33:54,083
You can't blame me entirely for not trusting you.

706
00:33:58,416 --> 00:33:59,541
About the student council transition,

707
00:33:59,541 --> 00:34:00,750
